Txt_Talk_Domdora_Out_SUB_0_ACTOR_0120_01.Text: *: Ne'er till the Lord of the Underworld lieth dead shall dawn break o'er this land once more.

Txt_Talk_Domdora_Out_SUB_0_ACTOR_0110_01.Text: *: Art thou the selfsame hero who did the Lord of the Underworld destroy?
*: Art thou the selfsame hero who did the Lord of the Underworld destroy?
*: But thou art a mere stripling! This is a miracle indeed!

Txt_Talk_Domdora_Out_SUB_0_ACTOR_0220_01.Text: *: The humble desert town of Damdara doth bid thee welcome, wanderer.

Txt_Talk_Domdora_Out_SUB_0_ACTOR_0210_01.Text: *: Hear ye, hear ye! The Lord of the Underworld is slain, and peace hath returned unto the land at last!

Txt_Talk_Domdora_Out_SUB_0_ACTOR_0320_01.Text: *: I know a seeecret! I know a seeecret! The flute is buried just south of the bath in Kol! ...Oops! Hee hee!

Txt_Talk_Domdora_Out_SUB_0_ACTOR_0310_01.Text: *: Hey you! Did you find the flute?
*: Oh, you did, did you? So my secret came in handy, did it? Hoorayyy!
*: Well, hurry up and find it, slowcoach!

Txt_Talk_Domdora_Out_SUB_0_ACTOR_0420_01.Text: *: Lo, though our world be covered in darkness, I have oftentimes seen a bright sparkling in yonder meadow.
*: It danceth among the undergrowth where the horses do prance and caper.

Txt_Talk_Domdora_Out_SUB_0_ACTOR_0410_01.Text: *: Lo...the light! Never have I seen it so bright... 'Tis like unto a dream!

Txt_Talk_Domdora_Out_SUB_0_ACTOR_0520_01.Text:
*: ♪ If the wandering minstrel Galen thou dost seeek...
Thou must journey due east toward fair Cantlin's keeep!
Shal-daral, hal-daral, deee! ♪

Txt_Talk_Domdora_Out_SUB_0_ACTOR_0520_02.Text:
*: ♪ Ohh, who shall end Galen's poor parents' lameeent...
Their son wand'reth far, and their patience is speeent! ♪
*: ♪ For he heedeth o'er all else the call of the roooad... ♪

*: ♪ And he visiteth not his ancestral abooode!
Yet his long ceaseless wand'rings have made him his naaame...
And the bards, they do sing of this troubadour's faaame! ♪

Txt_Talk_Domdora_Out_SUB_0_ACTOR_0510_01.Text: *: Brave warrior! Allow me to immortalise thy heroic deeds in sweet, sweet song!

*: ♪ Ohhh, a hero did slay the foul Underworld's Looord...
Did slay him away with a...lord-slaying, um...swooord! ♪
*: Ahem. Mayhap I am not quite the equal of the great Galen yet...

Txt_Talk_Domdora_Out_SUB_0_ACTOR_0720_01.Text: *: Journey south from this place, and continue then east once thou reachest the coast, and thou wilt reach mighty Cantlin.

*: Cross the first bridge that greets thee, heading eastwards from there. Though, make sure thou dost not do the same with the second bridge. Pay it no heed and follow the coast towards the north-east instead.

Txt_Talk_Domdora_Out_SUB_0_ACTOR_0710_01.Text: *: Shouldst thou travel south-east of this place, thou wilt reach in the end the mighty fortress of Cantlin.
*: Hm? What say'st thou? Thou knowest already of such things? But friend, I... I have naught else to tell thee...
*: In truth, I have naught else to tell any man... I seem capable only of repeating myself... Curious...

Txt_Talk_Domdora_Out_SUB_0_ACTOR_0910_01.Text: Even the horses seem to be grateful!

Txt_Talk_Domdora_Out_SUB_0_ACTOR_1020_01.Text: *: Today once more, a chill doth envelop the town. Without the sun's light, even the regions of the desert are grown cold.

Txt_Talk_Domdora_Out_SUB_0_ACTOR_1010_01.Text: *: Ahh, blessed be the sun in the heavens! Its warmth is like unto holy manna from heaven!

Txt_Talk_Domdora_Out_SUB_0_ACTOR_1110_01.Text: ...and a monster is revealed before your eyes!
{LEADER} calms the monster with a soothing voice and tells it about Monty's monster menagerie...

Txt_Talk_Domdora_Out_SUB_0_ACTOR_1210_01.Text: *: O benevolent Goddess! Thy will hath been done by <IfSolo(this,these)>, thy humble servant<IfSolo(,s)>! Let all men give thanks unto Thee!

Txt_Talk_Domdora_Out_SUB_0_ACTOR_1310_01.Text: *: I see a dragon near this town... No, wait... A true dragon it is not...
*: Hmm, I can no longer see the strange entity that prowled beyond the town limits... It has flown, but to where I cannot tell...

Txt_Talk_Domdora_Item_Shop_1F_SUB_0_ACTO.Text: *: From the bottom of my heart, I do thank thee. Thou hast brought the dawn at last!

Txt_Talk_Domdora_Weapon_Shop01_1F_SUB_0_.Text: *: Welcome unto thee, wanderer! Lo, the world is great, and the Goddess good! I say unto thee, all prices shall be halved!
*: What say'st thou? Thou no longer hast need of weapons and armour? Oh...
*: I wander the world in search of orichalcum, and yea, though I was told I might find it here, I see it not...
*: The Lord of the Underworld is truly slain? Verily, thou art mighty indeed!

Txt_Talk_Domdora_Weapon_Shop02_1F_SUB_0_.Text: *: Here in this place are sold weapons and armour. Unfortunately we are closed for now.
*: I am too much occupied with the naming of my next-born to do business...
*: Abimelech...? Magog...? Hmm, no, no... What manner of name wouldst thou favour, traveller?
*: Goddess be praised! At long last, the name of my child is decided!
*: Lo, the boy shall be called Magog!
*: His shall be a name that resoundeth around the world, and down through the ages!

Txt_Talk_Domdora_Weapon_Shop02_2F_SUB_0_.Text: *: Lo, a child is to be born unto me!
*: But he who hath begat this child is yet troubled in the matter of its naming. Such indecision befitteth him not!
*: He hath even been asking those who visit the shop their opinions.
*: I will certainly never forget the vexed look that adorned Ortega's great face when he too was consulted on the matter.
*: Lo, our child hath a name at last!
*: My husband hath set his heart upon...<6>Magog<9>. It is...unique...

Txt_Talk_Domdora_Inn_1F_SUB_0_ACTOR_0110.Text: *: Welcome, weary pilgrim, to the inn of the wayfarer.
*: But behold<--->the sun still beateth down full lustily from the heavens! Surely thou canst not rest while such glory yet abideth?
*: But hark at mine insolence! Without thine efforts on our behalf, such glory would yet be denied us! All hail thee, hero!

Txt_Talk_Domdora_Inn_2F_SUB_0_ACTOR_0120.Text: I am Lena, who once danced most successfully in the town of Asham.
But a customer, driven wild with love for me that I did not return, hounded me until I had no choice but to leave.

(sigh) I wonder if the proprietor of the establishment where I once danced is well...
Should you ever meet him, please, you must let him know that I am safe.

Txt_Talk_Domdora_Inn_2F_SUB_0_ACTOR_0110.Text: I once danced most successfully in the town of Asham.
But these are merely memories now. I have come to a new world, and here I shall make for myself a new life entirely.

Txt_Talk_Domdora_House01_1F_SUB_0_ACTOR_.Text: *: The venerable elder in the house next to mine own sneezeth relentlessly. My wrath waxes hot against him!
*: Yea, though the world be at peace, I, alas, am not. My venerable neighbour sneezeth yet relentlessly. Grr!

Txt_Talk_Domdora_House02_1F_SUB_0_ACTOR_.Text: *: Lo, who doth take my name in vain? Ahhhhhhhhh-CHOOOOOO!!!
*: Lo, who doth still, even now, take my name in vain?
*: Though mayhap I would be wise to give thanks that my name lingers yet on the lips of anybody at all...

*: Aye, at my age, 'tis a miracle indeed!
Ahh... Ahh... Ahhh-CHOO!!!

Txt_Talk_Domdora_House03_1F_SUB_0_ACTOR_.Text: *: Yea, the legends do tell of a realm above our own. A kingdom beyond the heavens. And in it, a wondrous Sphere of Light.
*: Could it be that, perchance, the Sphere's light might brighten our own realm, were it to be brought here?
*: The castle town of Tantegel hustleth and bustleth in preparation for a great celebration of the world's peace.

Txt_Talk_Domdora_Well_SUB_0_ACTOR_0120_0.Text: *: Alas, the water ebbeth lower by the day... I fear this town is not long for the world.
*: 'Twas e'er a struggle repelling the beasts of the desert, but what hope have we against thirst...?

Txt_Talk_Domdora_Well_SUB_0_ACTOR_0110_0.Text: *: Lo, the land above seemeth...brighter somehow. Whatever hath come to pass...?
*: Hm? What say'st thou? The dawn is come at last? But that can only mean...

*: The Lord of the Underworld is no more!
...And 'twas thou who didst smite him? By the Goddess, thou art mightier by far than thou seemest, wanderer...
